name: NAD(P)+ transhydrogenase (Si-specific)
classes: With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: The enzyme from Azotobacter vinelandii is a flavoprotein (FAD). It is Si-specific with respect to both NAD+ and NADP+. Also acts on deamino coenzymes [cf. EC 1.6.1.2 NAD(P)+ transhydrogenase (Re/Si-specific)].

references.title: The distribution and properties of transhydrogenase from animal tissues.
Stereospecificity for nicotinamide nucleotides in enzymatic and chemical hydride transfer reactions.
